On a side note, I would not use a `String` to represent a date, but rather a `LocalDate`: the [parse][1] method does exactly what you are trying to do and `LocalDate` replace `java.util.Date` and is immutable.

- This example below use such `LocalDate`, providing three constructors based on your code. Field are made final and only one constructor (the last) matters.
