You have an signed 8-bit 6Q2 format fixed point representation having a resolution of 2&lt;sup&gt;-2&lt;/sup&gt; (or 0.25).  You can look at this purely arithmetically:

The `int8_t` value of 11100011 is -29, but with the fixed point scaling that is -29 x 0.25 = -7.25.

Or then in terms of 2&#39;s compliment bit values which for an 8 bit *integer* are:

-2&lt;sup&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; (-128&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; (64&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; (32&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; (16&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; (8&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; (4&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; (2&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;0&lt;/sup&gt; (1&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;

but the Q2 fixed point shifts those place values by 2 as follows:

-2&lt;sup&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; (-32&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; (16&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; (8&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; (4&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; (2&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;0&lt;/sup&gt; (1&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;-1&lt;/sup&gt; (0.5&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
 2&lt;sup&gt;-2&lt;/sup&gt; (0.25&lt;sub&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;

